  "text": "A mean gene diversity (expected heterozygosity, He) of 0.67 was observed across the sorghum global composite collection, with values ranging from 0.24 (mSbCIR246) to 0.94 (Sb5-206) for individual markers (Table 2 ). Even though SbAGB02 produced the highest number of alleles [CITATION_1] , it presented an intermediate He value of 0.67 because 92% of these alleles can be considered as rare (74% below 1% frequency). With the exception of mSbCIR248, which had an unusually high observed heterozygosity (Ho) value of 0.23, the Ho values ranged from 0.01 (mSbCIR246) to 0.06 (Xtxp015) with a mean of 0.03. Its outstanding Ho value suggests that marker mSbCIR248 may have detected more than one polymorphic locus, but this is not confirmed yet by in-silico hybridisation to the complete reference sorghum sequence.",
